@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam actorStyle awesome

title TunSociety - Moderation Use Case Diagram

actor User
actor Moderator
actor Admin

rectangle "TunSociety Moderation" {
  usecase "Submit moderated content" as UC_Submit
  usecase "Analyze content" as UC_Analyze
  usecase "Allow content" as UC_Allow
  usecase "Flag content for review" as UC_Flag
  usecase "Block content" as UC_Block
  usecase "Record moderation result" as UC_Record
  usecase "Issue warning" as UC_Warning
  usecase "Freeze account" as UC_Freeze

  usecase "Review flagged content" as UC_ReviewFlagged
  usecase "Review warnings" as UC_ReviewWarnings
  usecase "Review freezes" as UC_ReviewFreezes
  usecase "Review appeals" as UC_ReviewAppeals
  usecase "Update appeal status" as UC_UpdateAppeal
  usecase "Accept freeze appeal" as UC_AcceptAppeal
  usecase "Audit moderation actions" as UC_Audit
}

User --> UC_Submit

Moderator --> UC_ReviewFlagged
Moderator --> UC_ReviewWarnings
Moderator --> UC_ReviewFreezes
Moderator --> UC_ReviewAppeals
Moderator --> UC_UpdateAppeal
Moderator --> UC_Audit

Admin --> UC_ReviewFlagged
Admin --> UC_ReviewWarnings
Admin --> UC_ReviewFreezes
Admin --> UC_ReviewAppeals
Admin --> UC_UpdateAppeal
Admin --> UC_Audit

UC_Submit .> UC_Analyze : <<include>>
UC_Analyze .> UC_Record : <<include>>
UC_Analyze .> UC_Allow : <<extend>>
UC_Analyze .> UC_Flag : <<extend>>
UC_Analyze .> UC_Block : <<extend>>

UC_Block .> UC_Warning : <<include>>
UC_Block .> UC_Freeze : <<extend>>

UC_UpdateAppeal .> UC_AcceptAppeal : <<extend>>
UC_UpdateAppeal .> UC_Audit : <<include>>

note bottom
The current backend exposes moderator/admin appeal review,
but it does not yet expose a public user endpoint to submit appeals.
Freeze occurs only after 3 blocked violations.
Accepting a freeze appeal can unfreeze the account.
User appeal submission can be modeled later as a planned extension.
end note
@enduml
